   =20
      Syndication
   =20
 =20
In=C2=A0ancient news from yesterday:Angel investor Jason Calacanis, an earl=
y backer of Uber and Robinhood, is seeking to raise tens of millions of dol=
lars for a stake in Twitter as part of Elon Musk=E2=80=99s $44 billion agre=
ement to buy the social media company.=E2=80=9CWe are now collecting intere=
st to invest in Twitter with Elon Musk=E2=80=99s plan to take it private,=
=E2=80=9D Calacanis wrote in a message soliciting funds from his network of=
 high net worth individuals. CNBC viewed Calacanis=E2=80=99s email to prosp=
ective investors.The minimum investment required to participate is $250,000=
, Calacanis wrote, adding that the fees he collects for the deal will total=
 about $18,000. As manager of the fund, he=E2=80=99s also asking for 10% of=
 the carry, or the gains that come from the investment.I wonder how that pi=
tch is going today. Probably great, right? If you liked this deal at $54.20=
, you like it even more at =E2=80=9CMusk being annoying to get leverage to =
reprice the deal.=E2=80=9D He really is going to achieve his dream of takin=
g a company private while still having lots of relatively small-dollar enth=
usiastic retail shareholders, of just  shuffling the shareholder base to ma=
ke it Muskier. Meanwhile getting 10% of the profits for being friends with =
Musk is nice work if you can get it.
