olid; background-color: #ccc;"> how that=E2=80=99s going</a>:</p><blockquot=
e><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The stablecoin was trading below 20 cents on=
 Friday morning in London, according to Bloomberg data. The Luna token has =
sunk to virtually zero, compared with its all-time high of $119.51. Wider c=
rypto markets recovered, with Bitcoin rising as much as 8.4%. ...</p><p sty=
le=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The total amount of Luna tokens in circulation is up=
 from 1.46 billion yesterday to more than 6.5 trillion on Friday morning, a=
ccording to data from CoinMarketCap.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"marg=
in: 16px 0;">At 11 a.m., Luna was trading at $0.00008254, according to Coin=
MarketCap, give or take a zero or two, down about 99.99993% from its all-ti=
me high, give or take a nine or two. Just an absolutely pristine death spir=
al.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I want to tell this story in a differen=
t way. Ignore the stablecoin for a bit. Luna is a cryptocurrency, the crypt=
ocurrency of the Terra blockchain and ecosystem. That blockchain is, let=E2=
=80=99s assume, useful for something. I don=E2=80=99t actually know, but so=
me people seem to think that, or at least say it. =E2=80=9CThe Terra ecosys=
tem is one of the most vibrant in the crypto industry, with hundreds of pas=
sionate teams building category defining applications within,=E2=80=9D Terr=
a impresario Do Kwon <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/27705861.260608/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9zdGFibGVrd29uL3N0YXR1cy8xNTI0=
MzMxMTk0ODgzNTc5OTA1/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3c3ff389" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">tweeted on =
Wednesday</a>.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Let=E2=80=99s just ass=
ume that that=E2=80=99s true. People are building stuff on Terra, and Luna =
is the cryptocurrency of Terra. This makes Luna like Ether for the Ethereum=
 blockchain, or various other cryptocurrencies for various other blockchain=
s. If you think the ecosystem is growing and valuable and can be used to bu=
ild cool stuff, the price of the currency should go up; if you think it is =
moribund and pointless, the price should go down.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16=
px 0;">The prices of lots of cryptocurrencies has gone down this week, whic=
h suggests doubts about the viability of the crypto world generally. But th=
ey haven=E2=80=99t gone down=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>much. Which makes sens=
e. Some people are crypto believers, others are crypto skeptics, and events=
 in the world might change their minds, but gradually. It would be very str=
ange for everyone to wake up on Monday thinking =E2=80=9Cthe future of econ=
omics is crypto, HODL=E2=80=9D and then to wake up on Friday thinking =E2=
=80=9Cthis is all fake, sell everything.=E2=80=9D A trillion-dollar ecosyst=
em based essentially on collective social belief shouldn=E2=80=99t lose tha=
t value overnight.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Luna really did lose alm=
ost all of its value almost overnight. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/27705861.260608/aHR0cHM6Ly9jb2lubWFya2V0Y2FwLmNvbS9jdX=
JyZW5jaWVzL3RlcnJhLWx1bmEvaGlzdG9yaWNhbC1kYXRhLw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0=
513fdf9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">A week ago</a> there were about 343 million Luna outstandi=
ng with a total value of $26.5 billion, today there are 6.5 trillion Luna o=
utstanding with a total value of, let=E2=80=99s face it, nothing. (CoinMark=
etCap says about $540 million, but that does not reflect the price at which=
 you could sell a trillion Luna.) A $26 billion ecosystem completely evapor=
ated.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Did that happen because people =
lost faith in that ecosystem? I mean, sure, yeah; the=C2=A0<em>main=C2=A0</=
em>job of that ecosystem was surely to preserve the value of a $1 stablecoi=
n, and it manifestly failed.=C2=A0But, again, that=E2=80=99s a weird thing =
to happen overnight. The people passionately building apps in the Terra eco=
system last week didn=E2=80=99t lose all their passion this week.=C2=A0</p>=
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But we can=E2=80=99t ignore the stablecoin. So=
me people were passionate believers in Terra, building apps on its blockcha=
in, buying Luna as a bet on its long-term potential. Other people, though, =
bought <em>UST</em>, not because they were betting on Terra but because the=
y wanted a safe place in the crypto world to put their dollars. (And <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27705861.260608/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cubm90Ym9yaW5nLmNvL3AvdGVycmEtdG8tdGhlLW1vb24tYW5kLWJhY2s_cz1y/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB094fb78c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">earn 19.5% interest</a>, sure.) UST wa=
s not an equity bet on the value of the Terra ecosystem and the passion of =
its developers; UST was a=C2=A0<em>safe asset</em>.</p><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;"><em>Safe assets are much riskier than risky ones</em>. This is I t=
hink the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27705861.=
260608/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubmJlci5vcmcvc3lzdGVtL2ZpbGVzL3dvcmtpbmdfcGFwZXJzL3cx=
Nzc3Ny93MTc3NzcucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB29177eb0" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">deep lesson=
</a> of the 2008 financial crisis, and crypto loves re-learning the lessons=
 of traditional finance. <em>Systemic=C2=A0</em>risks live in safe assets. =
Equity-like assets =E2=80=94=C2=A0tech stocks, Luna, Bitcoin =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0are risky, and everyone knows they=E2=80=99re risky, and everyone accept=
s the risk. If your stocks or Bitcoin go down by 20% you are sad, but you a=
re not that surprised. And so most people arrange their lives in such a way=
 that, if their stocks or Bitcoin go down by 20%, they are not=C2=A0<em>rui=
ned.</em></p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand safe assets =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0AAA mortgage securities, bank deposits, stablecoins =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0are not supposed to be risky, and people rely on them being worth wha=
t they say they=E2=80=99re worth, and when people lose even a little bit of=
 confidence in them they crack completely.=C2=A0Bitcoin is valuable at $50,=
000 and somewhat less valuable at $40,000. A stablecoin is valuable at $1.0=
0 and worthless at $0.98. If it hits $0.98 it might as well go to zero. And=
 now it might!</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I have in the past told the =
story of TerraUSD and Luna <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/27705861.260608/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydG=
ljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtMTEvdGVycmEtZmxvcHM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDUxMzIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmd=
